item.title: 🌕 Lipoma
item.description: Sebaceous cyst # When an opening of one sebaceous glands becomes blocked, it distends with sebum, and becomes a sebaceous cyst. History # Duration - present for some years Symptoms - Multiplicity often multiple Examination # Site - They are found in the hairy parts of the body. The scalp, scrotum, neck are the common sites. NB: No sebaceous glands on the palms and soles. Shape and size - Tense and spherical.
